    "usage": "<!-- Usage guidance for Button. Editable — author freely, then run `npm run build:docs-data`. -->\n\nUse Button for the actions on a view. Reserve the `Primary` variant for the single most important action in a region — never show two primary buttons side by side. `Secondary` is the default for most actions, `Tertiary` for low-emphasis or repeated ones, and `Positive`/`Destructive` only when the outcome is genuinely additive or irreversible.\n\n- Do lead each view with one clear primary action.\n- Do use `Small` only in dense toolbars and table rows.\n- Don't use `Destructive` for routine actions — it is reserved for delete/remove.\n- Don't pair an icon with a label that just repeats it; the icon should add meaning."
